cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.MM

The paper deals with data detection in large wireless systems with multiple antennas, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of semidefinite relaxation and optimization techniques also suggests a possible fit with the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the development of hardware designs for FPGA and ASIC implementations suggests a possible fit with the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
